-- Olympus to set up internal teams on governance, operational
-- 
-- Mon Nov 28, 2011 9:36pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/11/29/us-olympus-reforms-idUSTRE7AS06M20111129

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Olympus Corp will set up internal teams to examine possible governance reforms and changes to its operational structure as it moves to recover from an accounting scandal, according to an internal memo to employees from President Shuichi Takayama obtained by Reuters on Tuesday. 
 The teams will report to Takayama and will aim to complete their work as quickly as possible, according to the memo, dated November 28. (Reporting by Reiji Murai and Maki Shiraki; Writing by Edmund Klamann; Editing by  Edwina Gibbs )